00044 real_t getStatus( returnValue returnvalue )
00045 {
00046         /* determine status from returnvalue */
00047         switch ( returnvalue )
00048         {
00049                 case SUCCESSFUL_RETURN:
00050                         return 0.0;
00051 
00052                 case RET_MAX_NWSR_REACHED:
00053                         return 1.0;
00054 
00055                 case RET_INIT_FAILED_INFEASIBILITY:
00056                 case RET_HOTSTART_STOPPED_INFEASIBILITY:
00057                         return -2.0;
00058                 
00059                 case RET_INIT_FAILED_UNBOUNDEDNESS:
00060                 case RET_HOTSTART_STOPPED_UNBOUNDEDNESS:
00061                         return -3.0;
00062                         
00063                 default:
00064                         return -1.0;
00065         }
00066 }

00072 returnValue smartDimensionCheck(        real_t** input, unsigned int m, unsigned int n, BooleanType emptyAllowed,
00073                                                                         const mxArray* prhs[], int idx
00074                                                                         )
00075 {
00076         /* If index is negative, the input does not exist. */
00077         if ( idx < 0 )
00078         {
00079                 *input = 0;
00080                 return SUCCESSFUL_RETURN;
00081         }
00082 
00083         /* Otherwise the input has been passed by the user. */
00084         if ( mxIsEmpty( prhs[ idx ] ) )
00085         {
00086                 /* input is empty */
00087                 if ( emptyAllowed == BT_TRUE )
00088                 {
00089                         *input = 0;
00090                         return SUCCESSFUL_RETURN;
00091                 }
00092                 else
00093                 {
00094                         char msg[200];
00095                         snprintf(msg, 199, "ERROR (qpOASES): Empty argument %d not allowed!", idx+1);
00096                         mexErrMsgTxt( msg );
00097                         return RET_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
00098                 }
00099         }
00100         else
00101         {
00102                 /* input is non-empty */
00103                 if ( ( mxGetM( prhs[ idx ] ) == m ) && ( mxGetN( prhs[ idx ] ) == n ) )
00104                 {
00105                         *input = (real_t*) mxGetPr( prhs[ idx ] );
00106                         return SUCCESSFUL_RETURN;
00107                 }
00108                 else
00109                 {
00110                         char msg[200];
00111                         snprintf(msg, 199, "ERROR (qpOASES): Input dimension mismatch for argument %d ([%ld,%ld] ~= [%d,%d]).", 
00112                                         idx+1, (long int)mxGetM(prhs[idx]), (long int)mxGetN(prhs[idx]), m, n);
00113                         mexErrMsgTxt( msg );
00114                         return RET_INVALID_ARGUMENTS;
00115                 }
00116         }
00117 
00118         return SUCCESSFUL_RETURN;
00119 }

00125 returnValue convertFortranToC( const real_t* const A_for, int nV, int nC, real_t* const A )
00126 {
00127         int i,j;
00128 
00129         for ( i=0; i<nC; ++i )
00130                 for ( j=0; j<nV; ++j )
00131                         A[i*nV + j] = A_for[j*nC + i];
00132 
00133         return SUCCESSFUL_RETURN;
00134 }

00140 BooleanType hasOptionsValue( const mxArray* optionsPtr, const char* const optionString, double** optionValue )
00141 {
00142         mxArray* optionName = mxGetField( optionsPtr,0,optionString );
00143         
00144     if( !mxIsEmpty(optionName) )
00145         {
00146                 if ( ( mxGetM( optionName ) != 1 ) || ( mxGetN( optionName ) != 1 ) )
00147                         mexErrMsgTxt( "ERROR (qpOASES_options): Option has to be a numerical constant." );
00148 
00149                 *optionValue = mxGetPr( optionName );
00150                 return BT_TRUE;
00151         }
00152         
00153         return BT_FALSE;
00154 }

00266 void allocateOutputs(   int nlhs, mxArray* plhs[], int nV, int nC = 0, int nP = 1
00267                                                 )
00268 {
00269         /* Create output vectors and assign pointers to them. */
00270         plhs[0] = mxCreateDoubleMatrix( nV, nP, mxREAL );
00271 
00272         if ( nlhs >= 2 )
00273         {
00274                 plhs[1] = mxCreateDoubleMatrix( 1, nP, mxREAL );
00275 
00276                 if ( nlhs >= 3 )
00277                 {
00278                         plhs[2] = mxCreateDoubleMatrix( 1, nP, mxREAL );
00279 
00280                         if ( nlhs >= 4 )
00281                         {
00282                                 plhs[3] = mxCreateDoubleMatrix( 1, nP, mxREAL );
00283 
00284                                 if ( nlhs == 5 )
00285                                 {
00286                                         plhs[4] = mxCreateDoubleMatrix( nV+nC, nP, mxREAL );
00287                                 }
00288                         }
00289                 }
00290         }
00291 }

00296  */
00297 void obtainOutputs( int k, QProblemB* qp, returnValue returnvalue, int nWSRin,
00298                                         int nlhs, mxArray* plhs[], int nV, int nC = 0
00299                                         )
00300 {
00301         /* Create output vectors and assign pointers to them. */
00302         double* x = mxGetPr( plhs[0] );
00303         qp->getPrimalSolution( &(x[k*nV]) );
00304 
00305         if ( nlhs >= 2 )
00306         {
00307                 double* obj = mxGetPr( plhs[1] );
00308                 obj[k] = qp->getObjVal( );
00309 
00310                 if ( nlhs >= 3 )
00311                 {
00312                         double* status = mxGetPr( plhs[2] );
00313                         status[k] = getStatus( returnvalue );
00314 
00315                         if ( nlhs >= 4 )
00316                         {
00317                                 double* nWSRout = mxGetPr( plhs[3] );
00318                                 nWSRout[k] = (real_t) nWSRin;
00319 
00320                                 if ( nlhs == 5 )
00321                                 {
00322                                         double* y = mxGetPr( plhs[4] );
00323                                         qp->getDualSolution( &(y[k*(nV+nC)]) );
00324                                 }
00325                         }
00326                 }
00327         }
00328 }
